<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>get a break • have a break</xh5><p> <i>get a break—</i>1. take time off from an activity: It was hard for me because whenever I <u>got a break</u> from school, I had to leave and see my other parent. 2. <i>(coll.)</i> get a good deal in a transaction, etc.: Our customers usually expect to <u>get a break</u> when they buy in quantity. 3. <i>(coll.)</i> get an opportunity or special consideration: He talked about racism and about how hard it is to <u>get a break</u> when you are Black. <i>Cf.: get all the breaks</i>—be fortunate; have luck: That fellow <u>gets all the breaks</u>! He’s been working here only six months, and he’s already been promoted to vice president!</p><p> <i>have a break</i>— = get a break 1: Finally, I told him I’d interview him over lunch, when he <u>had a break</u>.</p> </entry>
